{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":919,"text":"So, I have an overlooked\nbut potentially lucrative"},{"time":5285,"text":"investment opportunity for you."},{"time":8447,"text":"Over the past 10 years in the UK,"},{"time":10885,"text":"the return on burial plots\nhas outperformed the UK property market"},{"time":14344,"text":"by a ratio of around three to one."},{"time":17924,"text":"There are private cemeteries being set up\nwith plots for sale to investors,"},{"time":21770,"text":"and they start at around 3,900 pounds."},{"time":24938,"text":"And they're projected to achieve\nabout 40 percent growth."},{"time":28484,"text":"The biggest advantage is that this\nis a market with continuous demand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35996,"text":"Now, this is a real proposition,"},{"time":38085,"text":"and there are companies out there\nthat really are offering this investment,"},{"time":42555,"text":"but my interest in it is quite different."},{"time":45713,"text":"I'm an architect and urban designer,"},{"time":47779,"text":"and for the past year and a half,"},{"time":49394,"text":"I've been looking at approaches\nto death and dying"},{"time":52418,"text":"and at how they've shaped our cities\nand the buildings within them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56515,"text":"So in the summer,\nI did my first exhibition"},{"time":59699,"text":"on death and architecture in Venice,"},{"time":62239,"text":"and it was called \"Death in Venice.\""},{"time":64563,"text":"And because death is a subject"},{"time":66588,"text":"that many of us find quite\nuncomfortable to talk about,"},{"time":69669,"text":"the exhibition was designed\nto be quite playful,"},{"time":72018,"text":"so that people would\nliterally engage with it."},{"time":74882,"text":"So one of our exhibits\nwas an interactive map of London"},{"time":78451,"text":"which showed just how much\nof the real estate in the city"},{"time":81493,"text":"is given over to death."},{"time":83467,"text":"As you wave your hand across the map,"},{"time":85673,"text":"the name of the piece of real estate --\nthe building or the cemetery --"},{"time":89202,"text":"is revealed."},{"time":90733,"text":"And those white shapes that you can see,"},{"time":93497,"text":"they're all of the hospitals and hospices"},{"time":96430,"text":"and mortuaries and cemeteries in the city."},{"time":99185,"text":"In fact, the majority are cemeteries."},{"time":101652,"text":"We wanted to show that, even though\ndeath and burial are things"},{"time":106378,"text":"that we might not think about,"},{"time":107893,"text":"they're all around us, and they're\nimportant parts of our cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112035,"text":"So about half a million people\ndie in the UK each year,"},{"time":116519,"text":"and of those, around a quarter\nwill want to be buried."},{"time":119572,"text":"But the UK, like many\nWestern European countries,"},{"time":123536,"text":"is running out of burial space,"},{"time":125235,"text":"especially in the major cities."},{"time":127670,"text":"And the Greater London Authority\nhas been aware of this for a while,"},{"time":131210,"text":"and the main causes are population growth,"},{"time":134702,"text":"the fact that existing\ncemeteries are almost full."},{"time":137567,"text":"There's a custom in the UK that graves\nare considered to be occupied forever,"},{"time":141898,"text":"and there's also development pressure --\npeople want to use that same land"},{"time":145649,"text":"to build houses or offices or shops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149896,"text":"So they came up with a few solutions."},{"time":151721,"text":"They were like, well, maybe we can\nreuse those graves after 50 years."},{"time":155788,"text":"Or maybe we can bury people,\nlike, four deep,"},{"time":158125,"text":"so that four people can be buried\nin the same plot,"},{"time":161137,"text":"and we can make more efficient use\nof the land that way,"},{"time":163804,"text":"and in that way, hopefully London\nwill still have space to bury people"},{"time":167168,"text":"in the near future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169106,"text":"But, traditionally, cemeteries\nhaven't been taken care of"},{"time":171792,"text":"by the local authority."},{"time":173556,"text":"In fact, the surprising thing is that\nthere's no legal obligation"},{"time":176946,"text":"on anyone in the UK\nto provide burial space."},{"time":180499,"text":"Traditionally, it's been done\nby private and religious organizations,"},{"time":185306,"text":"like churches and mosques and synagogues."},{"time":188510,"text":"But there's also occasionally\nbeen a for-profit group"},{"time":192459,"text":"who has wanted to get in on the act."},{"time":194500,"text":"And, you know, they look at\nthe small size of a burial plot"},{"time":198029,"text":"and that high cost,"},{"time":199721,"text":"and it looks like there's\nserious money to be made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202580,"text":"So, actually, if you want to go out\nand start your own cemetery,"},{"time":206318,"text":"you kind of can."},{"time":207765,"text":"There was this couple in South Wales,"},{"time":209925,"text":"and they had a farmhouse\nand a load of fields next to it,"},{"time":213185,"text":"and they wanted to develop the land."},{"time":215340,"text":"They had a load of ideas."},{"time":216765,"text":"They first thought about making\na caravan park,"},{"time":219903,"text":"but the council said no."},{"time":221641,"text":"And then they wanted to make a fish farm"},{"time":223633,"text":"and again the council said no."},{"time":225751,"text":"Then they hit on the idea\nof making a cemetery"},{"time":228446,"text":"and they calculated that by doing this,"},{"time":230526,"text":"they could increase\nthe value of their land"},{"time":233067,"text":"from about 95,000 pounds\nto over one million pounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238802,"text":"But just to come back to this idea\nof making profit from cemeteries,"},{"time":243585,"text":"like, it's kind of ludicrous, right?"},{"time":246267,"text":"The thing is that the high cost\nof those burial plots"},{"time":249804,"text":"is actually very misleading."},{"time":251944,"text":"They look like they're expensive,"},{"time":253755,"text":"but that cost reflects the fact that\nyou need to maintain the burial plot --"},{"time":257981,"text":"like, someone has to cut the grass\nfor the next 50 years."},{"time":261313,"text":"That means it's very difficult\nto make money from cemeteries."},{"time":264234,"text":"And it's the reason that normally\nthey're run by the council"},{"time":267083,"text":"or by a not-for-profit group."},{"time":269103,"text":"But anyway, the council granted\nthese people permission,"},{"time":271778,"text":"and they're now trying\nto build their cemetery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274253,"text":"So just to explain to you\nkind of how this works:"},{"time":277597,"text":"If I want to build something in the UK,"},{"time":279678,"text":"like a cemetery for example,"},{"time":281894,"text":"then I have to apply\nfor planning permission first."},{"time":284892,"text":"So if I want to build a new\noffice building for a client"},{"time":289126,"text":"or if I want to extend my home"},{"time":291404,"text":"or, you know, if I have a shop\nand I want to convert it into an office,"},{"time":295197,"text":"I have to do a load of drawings,"},{"time":296752,"text":"and I submit them\nto the council for permission."},{"time":299212,"text":"And they'll look at things like\nhow it fits in the surroundings."},{"time":303193,"text":"So they'll look at what it looks like."},{"time":305249,"text":"But they'll also think about things\nlike what impact is it going to have"},{"time":308869,"text":"on the local environment?"},{"time":310368,"text":"And they'll be thinking about things like,"},{"time":312432,"text":"is this thing going to cause pollution"},{"time":314297,"text":"or is there going to be a lot of traffic"},{"time":316249,"text":"that wants to go to this thing\nthat I've built?"},{"time":318606,"text":"But also good things."},{"time":320010,"text":"Is it going to add local services\nlike shops to the neighborhood"},{"time":323351,"text":"that local people would like to use?"},{"time":326183,"text":"And they'll weigh up the advantages\nand the disadvantages"},{"time":328901,"text":"and they'll make a decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330908,"text":"So that's how it works if I want\nto build a large cemetery."},{"time":335356,"text":"But what if I've got a piece of land"},{"time":337374,"text":"and I just want to bury\na few people, like five or six?"},{"time":341533,"text":"Well, then -- actually, I don't need\npermission from anyone!"},{"time":345850,"text":"There's actually almost no regulation\nin the UK around burial,"},{"time":350240,"text":"and the little bit that there is,\nis about not polluting water courses,"},{"time":353907,"text":"like not polluting rivers or groundwater."},{"time":356962,"text":"So actually, if you want to go\nand make your own mini-cemetery,"},{"time":360010,"text":"then you can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361329,"text":"But I mean, like -- really,\nwho does this? Right?"},{"time":366011,"text":"Well, if you're an aristocratic family\nand you have a large estate,"},{"time":369653,"text":"then there's a chance that you'll\nhave a mausoleum on it,"},{"time":372360,"text":"and you'll bury your family there."},{"time":374708,"text":"But the really weird thing"},{"time":376891,"text":"is that you don't need to have\na piece of land of a certain size"},{"time":380284,"text":"before you're allowed\nto start burying people on it."},{"time":382910,"text":"And so that means that, technically,"},{"time":384879,"text":"this applies to, like, the back garden\nof your house in the suburbs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388592,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":390370,"text":"So what if you wanted\nto try this yourself at home?"},{"time":394418,"text":"Well, there's a few councils\nthat have guidance on their website"},{"time":398490,"text":"which can help you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399901,"text":"So, the first thing that they tell you"},{"time":402019,"text":"is that you need to have a certificate\nof burial before you can go ahead --"},{"time":405779,"text":"you're not allowed to just murder people\nand put them under the patio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409151,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412253,"text":"They also tell you that you need to keep\na record of where the grave is."},{"time":416080,"text":"But that's pretty much it\nfor formal requirements."},{"time":418737,"text":"Now, they do warn you that\nyour neighbors might not like this,"},{"time":421763,"text":"but, legally speaking, there's almost\nnothing that they can do about it."},{"time":425690,"text":"And just in case any of you\nstill had that profit idea in your mind"},{"time":430880,"text":"about how much those burial plots cost"},{"time":433165,"text":"and how much money\nyou might be able to make,"},{"time":435537,"text":"they also warn that it might cause\nthe value of your house"},{"time":438307,"text":"to drop by 20 percent."},{"time":440515,"text":"Although, actually, it's more likely"},{"time":442286,"text":"that no one will want to buy\nyour house at all after that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446341,"text":"So what I find fascinating about this"},{"time":448924,"text":"is the fact that it kind of sums up\nmany of our attitudes towards death."},{"time":454280,"text":"In the UK, and I think that the figures\nacross Europe are probably similar,"},{"time":458720,"text":"only about 30 percent of people\nhave ever talked to anyone"},{"time":461855,"text":"about their wishes around death,"},{"time":463571,"text":"and even for people over 75,"},{"time":465505,"text":"only 45 percent of people\nhave ever talked about this."},{"time":469464,"text":"And the reasons that\npeople give ... you know,"},{"time":472163,"text":"they think that their death is far off"},{"time":474008,"text":"or they think that they're going\nto make people uncomfortable"},{"time":476909,"text":"by talking about it."},{"time":478319,"text":"And you know, to a certain extent,"},{"time":480098,"text":"there are other people out there\nwho are taking care of things for us."},{"time":483760,"text":"The government has all this regulation\nand bureaucracy around things"},{"time":487465,"text":"like burying a death, for example,"},{"time":489722,"text":"and there's people like funeral directors"},{"time":491715,"text":"who devote their entire\nworking lives to this issue."},{"time":494335,"text":"But when it comes to our cities"},{"time":495865,"text":"and thinking about how\ndeath fits in our cities,"},{"time":498931,"text":"there's much less regulation\nand design and thought"},{"time":503004,"text":"than we might imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504344,"text":"So we're not thinking about this,"},{"time":506582,"text":"but all of the people we imagine\nare thinking about it --"},{"time":509506,"text":"they're not taking care of it either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511575,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512757,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}